cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.CR, cs.AR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on improving the performance of short TCP flows in data centers, which is a networking problem. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also a likely category as the paper deals with improving the performance of data center networks. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper proposes a new approach to improve the performance of data center networks. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) are less likely categories as the paper does not focus on these topics.
